\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
It is usually difficult to determine the required sample size for response-adapt
ive designs.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
This is because the allocation probabilities keep changing during a clinical
 trial when using response-adaptive design.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
For a fixed sample size, the number of patients assigned to each treatment
 is a random variable.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Therefore the power is also a random variable for a fixed sample size.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
In the literature, sample sizes of response-adaptive designs are calculated
 by ignoring the randomness of the allocations.
 
\end_layout

\end_deeper
